  "body": "This blog explains the issue: https://medium.com/@ConsenSys/are-you-really-using-sha-3-or-old-code-c5df31ad2b0. Ethereum uses **Keccak-256**, not **SHA-3**, which was standardized afterwards. \n\nI could myself prepare a PR with this improvements:\n- Add to Godeps `golang.org/x/crypto/sha3` with a small patch to expose Keccak-256: https://github.com/jimenezrick/crypto/commit/8802e1c340c41c8d290e6315609cfbcbdf1b6229 (this thin fork could be hosted in the Ethereum Github obviously)\n- Using upstream `crypto/sha3` gives some _extra performance_, tested running go test benchmark.\n- Remove old copied **SHA-3 code**.\n- Rename any code referencing **SHA-3** instead of **Keccak-256**\n",
